  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (152e200 2022-09-13T00:05:42.069519Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test --match \"test_arbitrum_relay\" -vvv\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSwitching between forks a bunch with some persistent contracts and if something reverts it sometimes doesn't show the actual error. Instead I get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value\r\nLocation: /Users/runner/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/revm-2.0.0/src/journaled_state.rs:383\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere is an example of this which calls into the persistent contract which switches the fork and immediately reverts: https://github.com/makerdao/dss-test/blob/23913aa31c44030d0a5b4e106e0276a08de84904/src/tests/IntegrationTest.t.sol#L173\r\n",
